The paper is about complexity results related to Nash equilibria in game theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also discusses computational complexity, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper mentions Bayes-Nash equilibrium and multiagent systems, which are topics related to artificial intelligence and multiagent systems, respectively, indicating that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses normal form games and stochastic games, which are topics related to algorithms and data structures, suggesting that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could also be a possible sub-category.
